# Format: one CVE per line, with a comment block above explaining the
# risk-acceptance decision. Never add a bare CVE with no justification -
# that is exactly the "silently ignored" anti-pattern this file exists to
# avoid (see task2-cicd/README.md fail-policy table).
#
# All entries below were found on the first real CI run against the
# python:3.12-slim-bookworm base image (Debian 12.15). Every one shows no
# fixed version yet upstream in Debian 12 as of the found date (Trivy
# status: "affected" or "fix_deferred") - these are OS-package CVEs in the
# base image, not in ledger-api's own code or Python dependencies. Risk
# accepted short-term because the app runs non-root, read-only-root-fs,
# all-capabilities-dropped (Task 1), behind mTLS + identity-scoped authz
# (Task 3) - none of these CVEs are remotely exploitable through the
# app's actual attack surface. Re-evaluated whenever the base image is
# next bumped (Debian security backports typically land within weeks).

# Found: 2026-07-20 | Owner: platform-team | Review-by: 2026-08-19
# libblkid/libuuid/bsdutils/mount - integer overflow in libblkid partition parsing
CVE-2026-53615

